                            <comment id="432461" author="adilger" created="Thu, 24 Oct 2024 07:09:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I speculate based on some customer issues that were filed separately, but haven&apos;t actually tested that this is happening.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if this is the case, we may need to do something like launch a periodic background task (e.g. every 16k mmap page accesses) to touch the DLM lock and reset its status in the LRU so that it is not being expired.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternately, if a DLM lock can be flagged when the mmap call first arrives, and then if the lock us about to be expired from the LRU some extra checking could be done if the VMA is still actively being used and then reset it back to the end of the LRU if active.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
